replies.body:
If you're warding the jungle around mid as you decide to push up, you shouldn't be falling victim to ganks that often. Granted, it's hard to know where some of those sneaky junglers are going to come from.


You could simply ask your jungler to help you take the tower? Map objectives are one of their responsibilities after all.

However, in the case of Syndra, if you've just used your ultimate to make your laner back, or kill them, you are in a relatively vulnerable state. This is true for most champions that have a large portion of their power budget on R. {{champion:1}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:45}} 

If you're frequently dying to ganks, maybe you could try out a champion that is a more consistent threat? That has a lot more impact without their ultimate. {{champion:13}} {{champion:63}} {{champion:163}} 

That way, at least you can fight back during attempted ganks, or perhaps not even get ganked at all? :)
